Are Your Friends Unknowingly Pulling You Down?  
Have you ever experienced a dramatic life change, only to discover a few years afterward that you no longer connect with your old friends?

We tend to make friends with people who are like ourselves. However, the corollary is true: **We tend to become like our closest friends**. Our friends influence us through conversations, experiences, and the ideas they promote through the lives they live.

This is neither good nor bad--it is simply a law of life. How we use it is up to us.

We are the average of the people we associate with most. If we want to grow, it’s up to us to intentionally pursue strong relationships with people who have gone further than we have. 

This is why I am a proponent of local masterminds: groups of individuals who come together to share insight and support for each other in their pursuit of excellence.

Within a mastermind, individuals access:

- Outside perspective into their problems  
- Insight into blind spots or hidden potential  
- Fresh ideas of how to overcome obstacles or implement a vision  
- Support through the ups and downs of pursuing their vision

Masterminds hold a secret not found among groups of friends. Since those within a mastermind are actively sharing insight with each other, they are constantly growing. The average of the group is always increasing, including yours.

Despite the rags-to-riches stories, none of us pull ourselves up by our own bootstraps. We rely on other people to help us find our blind spots, teach us things we don’t know, and maximize our potential. 

Gather people of sharp intellect, strong passion, and deep creativity around you. You will find your growth (and your business) increase dramatically.
